lvmcfg (0.25) unstable; urgency=low

  * Martin Michlmayr
    - Honour the "Go Back" button and stop rather than proceed.
      Closes: #238966
    - When creating a VG, don't complain that the VG exists already
      merely when another VG exists which contains the name of the
      new one (that is, if the name of the new one is a subset of the
      existing one).  Closes: #246969
    - Print an error if a new VG name overlaps with an existing
      device.  Closes: #245700
    - When creating a LV, set the maximum available size as the
      default.  Closes: #246883
    - Accept common terms for disk sizes, such as MB, and convert
      them into something LVM understands.
    - After setting up VGs and no PVs are available for more VGs,
      go back to the main menu and default to the LV menu.  Closes:
      #246884
    - Similarly, go to "leave" when there is no more free space after
      setting up LVs.
    - Add myself as uploader and to the copyright file.
  * Updated translations:
    - Norwegian (nn.po) by Håvard Korsvoll
    - Romanian (ro.po) by Eddy Petrisor
    - Albanian (sq.po) by Elian Myftiu

 -- Martin Michlmayr <tbm@cyrius.com>  Sun, 02 May 2004 19:37:30 +0100

